node.text:
The sexiest Sunset Strip modern ever conceived, where all of your wildest dreams can be realized. Live life in god mode; look out onto the world with the most seductive views that just reach out and kiss you. Walking distance from ground zero of the Sunset Strip and the finest dining and entertainment LA has to offer, 30-foot ceilings rise above Italian Sahara stone floors, encasing the ultimate living space. Featuring first-class accommodations, from your very own spa wellness retreat with a cryo chamber, hot yoga and salon, a full size movie theater, six sumptuously appointed bedrooms, and the show stopper: the red room. This is the space age entertainer’s compound: every facet controllable from any corner of the globe, even low orbit with the state of the art savant system. Don’t just take it from us: watch the video and experience this lifestyle for yourself.
Via: @lux.interiors 
By: @triblendmedia

node.text: Today @archdigest take you to 1300 Beverly Estates Dr. in Beverly Hills to tour a stunning mansion currently on the market for just shy of $38 million. With 12,500 square feet of indoor space and another 10,000 of outdoor decking, room to spread out would never be an issue. An 80 foot infinity edge pool and game room ensure that there’s always something for you and your guests to get up to. Plus, for those with a love of paleontology, an authentic 150 million year-old dinosaur fossil sits just inside the entryway.

node.title: Inside a $38M Beverly Hills Mansion With a 150M Year-Old Dinosaur Fossil

node.text:
As a rare long time resident of the coveted East Gate of Bel Air, there was no better visionary to procure the finest lot of the neighborhood. In 2011, a serene promontory on the elite Bel Air road called his name. Just moments from Sunset Boulevard, this hilltop nirvana was the ultimate canvas to channel his talent into the defining estate of Los Angeles. A culmination of a lifetime of seasoned style, knowledge, skills, and people: the groundwork was laid for his masterpiece.

The journey began with a hunt for the world’s most discerning stylistic eyes, most meticulous craftsmen, and keenest visionaries who could help Dr. Kanodia make his dream reality. The dramatic architecture drawn from the sketchbook of the revered Paul McClean, the stone laid by the artisans of Tyler Construction, the fastidious fit and finishes of Lynda Murray and Mass Beverly; it was the purest symphony of the greatest minds and skill that real estate had to offer.

Modern. Exotic. Timeless. Formed with surgical precision. From the lush landscape gardens to the striking water features, every inch of Dr. Kanodia’s desire was realized. Envisioned from day one as his dream personal home, every ounce of his passion and soul was poured in to create something truly remarkable. An era defining estate that exudes quality from every angle, 908 Bel Air is a masterpiece in every sense of the word. The grand scale is evident from the 29’ entryway ceilings to the expansive views spanning the snowcapped mountains of the Angeles forest to the offshore oasis of Catalina. 34,000 square feet of pure perfection. This home now is the Most Expensive House to Rent - $1.5 Million Dollars per month - Bel,Air CA

Video: @triblendmedia

Described as the pinnacle of modern luxury, no expense was spared to create this ultra luxurious Bel Air masterpiece residence. Designed by the renowned architect Paul McClean, this stunning 14,219 sq. ft. home includes unsurpassed features and five-star amenities perched high above the city of Los Angeles on one of the Platinum Triangle’s most coveted streets. The explosive city-to-ocean views and flawless architecture elevate this residence to more than just a home; it’s a work of art.

Featuring the sheer perfection of clean lines with free-flowing glass and marble, meticulously crafted with the finest elements, this trophy property was envisioned to be one of the great residences in the world. No detail was spared throughout the dramatic open floor plan that opens up to one of the best views in all of Bel Air. From the moment you enter, you are indulged with a true sense of seamless integration of luxury and a brilliant environment that features sweeping panoramic city views beyond compare, creating an unprecedented multisensory living experience.

Taking full advantage of the stunningly breathtaking views, this magnificent luxury residence features collapsible glass walls that open to the free-flowing interior spaces providing an almost incomparable transition between indoor and outdoor living. As you step over the threshold, an exquisite infinity-edge pool perfectly frames the breathtaking panoramic views out over the city and out beyond to the ocean. Built for those that appreciate the finer things in life, this incredible residence represents the epitome of prestigious luxury living in an oasis of spectacular architecture and sensational style.
By: @triblendmedia

With an exquisite juxtaposition of raw and refined materials, this incredible estate was designed with exceptional materials, planning, detail & furnishings by Spinnaker Development. Spinnaker’s newest and most innovative build to date incorporates traditional architectural materials and form while introducing a contemporary open floor plan concept, pursuing maximum ocean views. Dramatic and expansive indoor / outdoor living elements and modern technology are blended with custom and imported detailing to create a truly unique coastal living experience, ideal for the prestigious Cameo Shores Community. The gorgeous kitchen features a top of the line Wolf and Sub Zero suite with two Bosch dishwashers, beautiful Lumix countertops & a fully functional butler’s kitchen. The master suite has custom made furnishings, including a pop up television cabinet, automated window treatments, his & her Toto washlets, round soaking tub, all slab steam shower, all with the Pacific Ocean as a backdrop. The dramatic entry includes a custom built twelve-foot mahogany door with hydraulic pivot and provides breathtaking views out to the mosaic glass tiled infinity edge pool with a glass bottom cantilevered over the living space below. The lower level has a dedicated movie theater with acoustic paneling and 137” screen, a great room for the sports enthusiast with 6 panel 4K media wall, oversized bar with all the amenities, walk in wine cellar, private grotto, as well as a private lower level suite.
By: @triblendmedia

node.text:
In a quiet neighborhood minutes from the heart of Beverly Hills sits The Beverly Estate built by Boswell Construction, a 3-story Mega Mansion with Dinosaur Raptor Bones and real Fossil to greet you.  This Beverly Hills House captures panoramic views of the city below and ocean beyond. 
This stunning contemporary modern luxury home boasts one of the best view sites in all of Beverly Hills. Drive onto the 16,000 square foot compound including a double-height glass entry and grand panoramic views of LA. Chef's kitchen has 2 waterfall islands, butlers kitchen & walk-in pantry. Main floor is completed with dining room, double sided fireplace, living room, separate family room and sliding glass doors for seamless in/outdoor living. The custom designed staircase takes you to the 2nd floor master wing with morning kitchen, balcony & rooftop deck, completely separate from guest wing. Guest rooms include en-suite baths & sliding pocket doors disappear to reveal breathtaking views. Expansive main floor deck with outdoor dining & kitchen, & infinity pool with spa. Basement with theater, gym, additional guest room, wine wall & tasting area, 4-car garage with additional 4 car carport. Full turnaround drive up motor court

Built by Boswell Construction, this 12,500-square-foot home is filled with distinctive amenities and bespoke decorative elements. Enter the lower level from the terrace, which runs the length of the home's view-facing facade. This floor encompasses a game room, fitness studio, a 600-bottle wine wall and theater. The home's main level features a showroom garage, chef's kitchen and living areas. On the third level are 3 ensuite bedrooms and master suite. Additional features include an 80-foot-long infinity pool, motor court and smart home technology system. Located minutes from the entertainment of West Hollywood, The Beverly Estate is an architectural marvel ideal for entertaining and sophisticated everyday living.

By: @triblendmedia

Straddling the city's ultimate view corridor, this is one of only 15 homes on the "front row" of the Hollywood Hills, the ridgeline offering the best views in all of Los Angeles. Recently renovated with only the finest materials, the sun-soaked villa has skylights and dramatic walls of glass that effortlessly blend with organic hardwoods to create a world-class modern getaway above it all. Mature olive trees and drought-resistant plantings invoke the Italian Riviera, the spacious patios offer ample space for large-scale entertaining, and the infinity-edged pool faces endless sunset views. With unobstructed vistas from high above the entire city, from the DTLA skyline to the Pacific Ocean and Catalina Island, you'll immediately feel at home with the stars.

Breaking barriers of interior design and architecture with the cannabis lounge inside the mansion. The first of its kind. ✅

Listed for €2,500,000 - Its large private plot of 743 m2 is situated along the beach protection line ensuring unobstructed sea views and direct access to the sea, since nothing can be built in front of it. It features four en-suite bedrooms and spacious living spaces in a building area of 267 m2. The optional lower ground floor, which is available in a number of alternative internal layout options, increases the building area to 387 m2 offering additional space for more rooms, such as, bedrooms, gym, games room, sauna, laundry room, cellar and storage.
Listed by: @nestseekers

@Michael_Kollosche from @Kollosche_ SOLD this spectacular waterfront mansion that is in a league of its own. Experience the highest standard of luxury waterfront living in this striking Sovereign Islands estate which delivers exquisite design in an exclusive private locale.

'Bellagio' makes a bold statement from the street where curved concrete architecture establishes an impressive presence. Expectations are exceeded inside where a newly completed renovation achieves seamless, sensual sophistication over four levels. 

A sleek black kitchen, spacious living and dining zones spill onto an outdoor balcony where a panoramic vista spans the Broadwater to the hinterland. An indoor leisure room complete with heated pool and a built-in BBQ kitchen is the ultimate year-round entertaining space. 

Deep water mooring on a 24.4 metre pontoon caters for luxury cruisers of up to 100ft with bridge-free passage to the ocean. Land-based toys are also encouraged with a secure eight-car garage finished in a showroom style.

Contact @Michael_Kollosche for more information
